SIMPLE: frontal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frontal
<hw>Fron"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>frontal</ets>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to the front part; being in
front</def>; esp. <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <def>Of or pertaining to the
forehead or the anterior part of the roof of the brain case; <as>as, the
<ex>frontal</ex> bones</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frontal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Frontal
<hw>Fron"tal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>frontal</ets>,
<ets>fronteau</ets>, OF. <ets>Frontel</ets>, <ets>frontal</ets>, L.
<ets>frontale</ets> an ornament for the forehead, frontlet. See
<er>Front</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something worn on the forehead
or face; a frontlet</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An ornamental band for
the hair.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The metal face guard
of a soldier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 599 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A little pediment over a door or
window.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A movable, decorative member in
metal, carved wood, or, commonly, in rich stuff or in embroidery,
covering the front of the altar. Frontals are usually changed according
to the different ceremonies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A medicament or application for
the forehead.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Quincy.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The frontal bone, or one of the
two frontal bones, of the cranium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Frontal hammer</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Frontal helve</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a forge hammer lifted by a
cam, acting upon a ⟦ldquo⟧tongue⟦rdquo⟧ immediately in front of the
hammer head.</cd> <rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj></cs></p>

<p><ent>Fron'tated</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Frontate</ent>⟦br⟧
